File: The South African Broadcasting Corporation. JOHANNESBURG - The SABC has stopped issuing retrenchment letters, following a heated staff meeting on Tuesday afternoon. The public broadcaster's COO Ian Plaatjies and Executive of News Pathiswa Magopeni held a meeting with angry staffers. READ: Union to fight SABC retrenchments Employees have told management they won't accept the latest round of restructuring, and are calling for the resignation of management. The cash-strapped SABC is planning to cut hundreds of jobs in the coming months. The broadcaster has recorded a loss of over R500-million in the 2019/2020 financial year.